incandescent /ˌɪnkænˈdɛsənt/

ADJ Incandescent substances or devices give out a lot of light when heated. 遇热发光的; 白炽的 [技术] 

例： ...incandescent gases. ...遇热发光的气体。 

2. ADJ If you describe someone or something as incandescent , you mean that they are very lively and impressive. 富有活力的; 热情洋溢的 [文学性] [usu ADJ n] 

例： Kerrie Mae had an extraordinary, incandescent personality. 嘉利•梅个性鲜明，热情洋溢。 

3. incandescence N-UNCOUNT 

例： She burned with an incandescence that had nothing to do with her looks. 她光彩照人，但这与其容貌无关。

